1
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:30,948
THE HUSBAND

2
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,410
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:39,039
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

4
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:42,124
EPISODE 4

5
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:01,770
You're home.

6
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:06,108
Where were you all night?

7
00:01:07,109 --> 00:01:08,402
Why are you out here?

8
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:10,320
You should be in bed.

9
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,574
You've been acting weird lately.

10
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,118
You're always late,
and I can never reach you.

11
00:01:20,581 --> 00:01:21,623
Something came up.

12
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:24,793
You couldn't even call me?

13
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:33,927
Where's Hayun?

14
00:01:36,305 --> 00:01:39,683
She kept asking for you
then fell asleep a while ago.

15
00:01:40,851 --> 00:01:41,852
Right.

16
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:48,567
What could possibly keep you out so late?

17
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:54,364
I told you,
something came up at the hospital.

18
00:01:58,869 --> 00:01:59,995
Honey.

19
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:03,040
Are you hiding something from me?

20
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:07,252
I'm not.

21
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,215
You sure there's nothing going on?

22
00:02:15,427 --> 00:02:16,428
I'm sure.

23
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:20,182
Fine.

24
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,561
Listen.

25
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:26,730
I'm your wife.

26
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:32,110
You have to tell me
if there is something going on.

27
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:36,614
I can tell you're having a hard time,
but you won't say anything.

28
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,123
Okay.

29
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:49,086
I just hope
there's really nothing going on.

30
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,592
But can I just say something?

31
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:57,886
You've changed so much.

32
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:01,515
I barely recognize you anymore.

33
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:15,070
Where's your wedding ring?

34
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:20,409
I took it off before surgery.
I probably left it in the office.

35
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:44,014
ACCESS RESTRICTED

36
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,391
ACCESS GRANTED

37
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:49,980
RESTRICTED ACCESS
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

38
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,054
Geez, you scared me.

39
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:24,972
What are you doing here so late?

40
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,057
You know,
I just left something in the office.

41
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:30,186
Must be pretty damn important.

42
00:04:30,187 --> 00:04:31,979
Hang in there, then. See you.

43
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:32,981
Okay.

44
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:35,567
Chiung.

45
00:04:36,651 --> 00:04:37,735
Yes?

46
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:39,613
What? You got something to say?

47
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:42,364
The thing is…

48
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,117
Sorry, let me take this real quick.

49
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,368
This is Choi.

50
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:49,079
Dr. Choi, it's me.
I'll cut right to the chase.

51
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:52,708
- Have you heard from Taeju at all?
- Yeah, what a coincidence.

52
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:54,168
Are you with him right now?

53
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:55,377
Yes.

54
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:57,963
The police are on their way,

55
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,549
so you have to keep him there,
no matter what.

56
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,010
Yeah, I got it.

57
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:08,933
Chiung, I'm so sorry.

58
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:10,434
I'll explain later!

59
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:20,361
RED LIGHT AND SPEEDING
SURVEILLANCE CAMERA

60
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:24,281
Captain, we got an update
on Kang's location.

61
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,366
Where?

62
00:05:25,367 --> 00:05:28,494
He was at Deoksam Intersection
at 9:46 p.m.

63
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:29,496
Heading that way.

64
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:43,342
Plate number 1228, please pull over.

65
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:44,760
Pull over, 1228.

66
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:52,101
Suspect vehicle is heading
toward Shinyu-dong.

67
00:05:52,102 --> 00:05:54,312
Units two and three, in pursuit.

68
00:06:01,403 --> 00:06:02,737
Kang Taeju!

69
00:06:03,238 --> 00:06:05,073
Pull over right now!

70
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,366
Stop being so reckless!

71
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,035
Cut him off! Get in front of him!

72
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,788
Damn it.

73
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:31,724
Turn around! Step on it!

74
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:35,812
Control, we lost the suspect
vehicle during pursuit. Plate number 1228.

75
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:52,971
Everyone, back up!

76
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,182
Keep them away!

77
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:05,401
Captain, it looks like he went
toward the main road.

78
00:08:05,402 --> 00:08:07,320
Go after him. He couldn't have gone far.

79
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,755
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

80
00:08:39,269 --> 00:08:42,938
TAKING ACCOUNTABILITY
FOR THE PEOPLE

81
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:45,692
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

82
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:01,708
Hey, stop!

83
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:06,545
-  Kang Taeju is over there!
-  Back up!

84
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:09,882
We found Kang Taeju. He's over there!

85
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:19,350
Go!

86
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:24,355
- That way!
-  Yes, sir!

87
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,078
Get to the second floor, now!

88
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:40,121
Yes, sir.

89
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:47,878
Where did he go?

90
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:50,131
Go the other way! Block him off!

91
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:57,722
What the hell, man? Stop!

92
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,182
What the hell are you doing?

93
00:10:00,183 --> 00:10:01,309
Get him!

94
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:04,104
Hey! Wait, Kang Taeju!

95
00:10:11,486 --> 00:10:12,945
- He's moving!
- That nutjob.

96
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:14,655
Kang Taeju, stop!

97
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:15,740
Kang Taeju!

98
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:17,908
Chase him down!

99
00:10:17,909 --> 00:10:18,992
- Hey, Kim.
- Sir?

100
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:21,162
- Request backup ASAP!
- Yes, sir.

101
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,917
Copy, Seongjin PD request for backup.

102
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:29,002
Two patrol units rolling immediately.

103
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:31,506
Detective unit to follow.

104
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:27,145
Seyun.

105
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,486
Let's put an end to this.

106
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,363
What?

107
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:40,658
I want a divorce.

108
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:45,371
That bastard.

109
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:52,712
My gosh! What was that?

110
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:19,071
Move!

111
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:20,073
Over there!

112
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:24,410
That way.

113
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:49,394
There you are.

114
00:12:56,359 --> 00:12:59,654
You think you can play games with cops?
You have the right to an attorney--

115
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:03,031
No!

116
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:28,016
No…

117
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:38,818
Kang Taeju…

118
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:44,157
You can't move your arms and legs?

119
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:49,119
Your spinal cord is damaged.

120
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,998
You'll damage your nerves permanently
if you try to move.

121
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,021
Don't move, okay?

122
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:26,949
Hold on…

123
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:34,373
There you go.

124
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:45,384
Hello, we need an ambulance.

125
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:49,471
Yeah, I'm at Ilseo Supply Center.

126
00:14:49,472 --> 00:14:53,101
There's a patient with spinal cord damage
in the stairwell down to the basement.

127
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:57,396
Yeah, he needs to get to a hospital, STAT.
So please hurry.

128
00:15:31,514 --> 00:15:36,435
THE HUSBAND

129
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:43,567
EMERGENCY SERVICES

130
00:15:43,568 --> 00:15:46,279
- Hey, Kim. You all right?
-  Wait, hold on.

131
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:49,282
Captain, Kang Taeju…

132
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,449
He took my gun.

133
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:52,702
Your gun?

134
00:15:53,327 --> 00:15:54,453
I'm sorry, sir.

135
00:15:59,834 --> 00:16:02,586
All right.
Don't worry about that right now.

136
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:04,255
Please take him to the hospital.

137
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:12,012
Hey, will he be okay?

138
00:16:12,013 --> 00:16:14,764
Well, we can't be sure
until we get to the hospital,

139
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:19,103
but thanks to the prompt first aid,
I think he'll be able to avoid the worst.

140
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,482
First aid?

141
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:29,112
Hey, put out an APB on Kang Taeju.

142
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:30,114
- I'm on it.
- Yes, sir.

143
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:22,959
EUMGOK, JUNSEONG

144
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:33,261
The doors are closing.

145
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:38,766
THIS TRAIN IS BOUND FOR JUNSEONG

146
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:19,348
I'm impressed, Kang Taeju.

147
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,733
You actually made it.

148
00:18:30,693 --> 00:18:32,111
Where's my wife right now?

149
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:34,572
Come with me.

150
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:58,721
NAMGANG LIVESTOCK DISTRIBUTION

151
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:50,523
Where are we?

152
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:54,984
I thought we were going to find my wife.

153
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:58,196
That's for you
to figure out from here on out.

154
00:19:58,197 --> 00:19:59,240
Excuse me?

155
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:05,538
Is this some kind of joke?

156
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,709
You said you knew
I didn't have my wife kidnapped.

157
00:20:10,793 --> 00:20:13,587
You said you'd help me find her.
So where is she right now?

158
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,929
NEUROSURGEON KANG TAEJU

159
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,599
SEYUN

160
00:20:33,691 --> 00:20:34,692
What the hell?

161
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:37,027
Are you working with that bastard?

162
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:38,821
Where is my wife?

163
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:42,408
Answer me!

164
00:20:43,451 --> 00:20:44,535
I told you.

165
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:47,370
It's up to you to figure it out now.

166
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:48,414
What?

167
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:50,540
Are you kidding me?

168
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:52,709
Do you want to die right here?

169
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:54,128
Where's Seyun?

170
00:20:57,423 --> 00:20:59,967
Where is Seyun? Where is she?

171
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,970
Have you ever killed a person before?

172
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:05,306
What?

173
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:09,017
You must have had
your opportunities as a doctor.

174
00:21:09,018 --> 00:21:12,271
There's only a fine line
between saving a life and taking one.

175
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:15,399
What the hell are you saying?

176
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:20,196
How far will Kang Taeju go for his wife?

177
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:25,201
Could he kill a person?

178
00:22:00,653 --> 00:22:01,654
Say hi.

179
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:03,697
That's my wife.

180
00:22:07,827 --> 00:22:09,578
If you can't find the bastard soon,

181
00:22:10,913 --> 00:22:12,873
your wife will end up like her too.

182
00:22:16,669 --> 00:22:19,338
That's why you're going to be my bait.

183
00:22:20,923 --> 00:22:22,550
You get your wife back,

184
00:22:24,385 --> 00:22:25,803
and I get to kill the bastard.

185
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,272
What, so that's your wife?

186
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:41,569
What does that even…

187
00:22:47,575 --> 00:22:49,200
PARK GYEONGMIN

188
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:50,744
OCCUPATION
PHOTOGRAPHY INSTRUCTOR

189
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:12,391
You know, you're right.

190
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:16,270
There's a fine line
between saving a life and taking one.

191
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:19,148
That's the trade I'm in.

192
00:23:20,441 --> 00:23:22,192
It demands absolute precision.

193
00:23:23,277 --> 00:23:26,947
A tenth of a millimeter can
either kill or save a person.

194
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:29,950
One nick to the brain stem
and they're dead on the table.

195
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:34,662
Catch the spinal nerve root,

196
00:23:34,663 --> 00:23:39,376
and they're looking at
a lifetime of intractable, burning pain.

197
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:43,714
Look, man.

198
00:23:46,717 --> 00:23:50,762
I don't care who's in that picture,
whether it's your wife or not.

199
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:52,389
I only care about one thing.

200
00:23:55,351 --> 00:23:56,894
Where's my wife?

201
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:20,417
What was that?

202
00:24:21,335 --> 00:24:23,337
What on earth is going on?

203
00:25:22,438 --> 00:25:23,439
Hello?

204
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,773
Hello? Are you in here?

205
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:28,609
How did you get out?

206
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:30,738
No time to explain.
We have to get out of here.

207
00:25:37,494 --> 00:25:39,162
Why won't this thing open?

208
00:25:39,163 --> 00:25:41,457
-  What? It won't open?
- No, it's…

209
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:45,376
I think I'll need the keys to this door.

210
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,211
Just save yourself while you can.

211
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:49,423
No, I can't just leave you. Just hang on.

212
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:11,236
I found the keys. Hold on.

213
00:26:11,862 --> 00:26:13,781
What? Really?

214
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:15,991
Not this one.

215
00:26:17,785 --> 00:26:19,161
Come on.

216
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:21,079
- Please.
-  Oh, no.

217
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:23,415
I don't think I stand a chance.

218
00:26:24,541 --> 00:26:27,294
Just get out of here.
You have to save yourself.

219
00:26:28,337 --> 00:26:31,507
Don't give up. You have to see
how your husband really feels.

220
00:26:42,101 --> 00:26:43,559
Got it.

221
00:26:55,489 --> 00:26:56,490
Ms. Ko.

222
00:26:58,784 --> 00:26:59,993
Where are you going?

223
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:20,055
The things you go through
because of your husband…

224
00:27:21,682 --> 00:27:22,891
Am I right?

225
00:27:29,398 --> 00:27:31,692
LEE SUHYEONG
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

226
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,681
Tell me.

227
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:05,559
Who really are you?

228
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:09,229
Why did you come looking for me?

229
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:12,441
Six years ago,

230
00:28:14,318 --> 00:28:15,736
my wife was abducted.

231
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:22,451
Just like your wife.

232
00:28:23,869 --> 00:28:25,202
SUSPECT INTERROGATION REPORT

233
00:28:25,203 --> 00:28:28,289
Yuseok, I'm going to ask you
one last time.

234
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:30,374
Where did you hide
the rest of the merchandise?

235
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:32,877
I don't know. How am I supposed to know?

236
00:28:32,878 --> 00:28:34,713
INCOMING CALL
GYEONGMIN

237
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:38,507
If you keep playing dumb
after I come back from this call,

238
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:40,384
you'll be dead tonight.

239
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:42,303
Be smart about this. Geez.

240
00:28:45,849 --> 00:28:47,350
Hey, honey. Don't wait up.

241
00:28:47,351 --> 00:28:49,560
I don't think I can make it home today.

242
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,396
Detective Lee Suhyeong?

243
00:28:56,485 --> 00:28:57,610
Yeah, who's this?

244
00:28:57,611 --> 00:29:00,155
And why do you have my wife's phone?

245
00:29:04,618 --> 00:29:06,828
GYEONGMIN

246
00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:13,626
What the hell?

247
00:29:13,627 --> 00:29:14,962
Keep it down.

248
00:29:15,963 --> 00:29:19,925
If the cops around you catch on,
I'll have no choice but to kill her.

249
00:29:24,388 --> 00:29:26,514
What do you want from me?

250
00:29:26,515 --> 00:29:28,100
Thirty million won in cash.

251
00:29:28,725 --> 00:29:31,894
In one hour, meet me
at Yeongjin Industrial Complex, alone.

252
00:29:51,748 --> 00:29:52,832
Yeah.

253
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:54,292
You see the door in front of you?

254
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,712
Leave the money there and walk away.

255
00:29:57,963 --> 00:30:01,882
- And my wife?
- I'll tell you where she is in 10 minutes.

256
00:30:17,899 --> 00:30:19,067
Where is she?

257
00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:22,029
Where is my wife?

258
00:30:25,365 --> 00:30:26,491
Tell me!

259
00:30:27,159 --> 00:30:29,119
Honey.

260
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:31,037
Gyeongmin.

261
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:35,624
You're okay, right? You all right?

262
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:36,834
I don't know.

263
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:38,170
You're not hurt, are you?

264
00:30:39,421 --> 00:30:41,506
I'm just really dizzy.

265
00:30:42,591 --> 00:30:46,344
Honey, what's going to happen to me?

266
00:30:49,347 --> 00:30:50,974
You're going to be fine.

267
00:30:52,517 --> 00:30:54,102
Just give me a minute.

268
00:30:56,521 --> 00:30:57,939
I'll be right there.

269
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,107
Hey, Detective.

270
00:31:00,108 --> 00:31:03,528
I think I made a huge mistake.

271
00:31:04,821 --> 00:31:05,905
What do you mean?

272
00:31:05,906 --> 00:31:11,535
Knowing how much you love your
wife, 30 million isn't going to cut it.

273
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:13,871
I should have asked
for at least 100 million.

274
00:31:13,872 --> 00:31:15,874
What the hell are you talking about?

275
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,542
We had an agreement.

276
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:22,964
Get me the additional 70 million
by 1 p.m., 2 days from now.

277
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,841
Listen, you prick.

278
00:31:25,842 --> 00:31:27,259
Insult me all you want,

279
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:29,303
but after you get me the money.

280
00:31:45,237 --> 00:31:51,534
JANUARY 31

281
00:31:57,457 --> 00:31:58,958
What took you so long?

282
00:31:58,959 --> 00:32:00,084
Where's my wife?

283
00:32:00,085 --> 00:32:01,586
I'm sorry, Detective.

284
00:32:02,212 --> 00:32:04,296
Something urgent came up.

285
00:32:04,297 --> 00:32:06,257
Leave the money by the pavilion,

286
00:32:06,258 --> 00:32:08,884
and I'll tell you
where she is in 10 minutes.

287
00:32:36,329 --> 00:32:38,038
8:15 P.M., JANUARY 31

288
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:40,167
8:16 P.M., JANUARY 31

289
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:08,028
Hello? What's going on here?

290
00:33:08,862 --> 00:33:10,739
I got you the money as promised.

291
00:33:12,407 --> 00:33:15,826
You should let my wife go now.

292
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:17,036
I know.

293
00:33:17,037 --> 00:33:19,371
I totally should let her go.

294
00:33:19,372 --> 00:33:23,210
But the thing is,
I don't think I'll be able to.

295
00:33:24,794 --> 00:33:26,379
What are you talking about?

296
00:33:27,631 --> 00:33:31,759
You asked for more money,
so I brought it for you.

297
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,261
Tell me about it.

298
00:33:33,929 --> 00:33:35,430
Why are you doing this?

299
00:33:36,765 --> 00:33:39,266
What's the reason?

300
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:43,605
Detective, do you really not know
why I'm doing this?

301
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:48,359
You're being punished for your wrongdoing.

302
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:50,153
I'm so sorry, sir.

303
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:54,907
I'm down on my knees
apologizing right now.

304
00:33:54,908 --> 00:33:56,492
I'm really sorry.

305
00:33:56,493 --> 00:34:00,371
What I've done is unacceptable. I'm sorry!

306
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:02,122
But could you please…

307
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:05,960
Could you please let my wife go?

308
00:34:05,961 --> 00:34:07,419
I'm begging you.

309
00:34:07,420 --> 00:34:09,046
So go ahead.

310
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:10,674
Tell me what you've done wrong.

311
00:34:13,635 --> 00:34:15,636
Why apologize when you don't know?

312
00:34:15,637 --> 00:34:16,638
Detective.

313
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:19,307
Just know this.

314
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:22,143
What happened to your wife

315
00:34:24,104 --> 00:34:25,689
is all on you.

316
00:34:27,315 --> 00:34:29,608
Sir, please.

317
00:34:29,609 --> 00:34:30,652
Hello?

318
00:34:31,278 --> 00:34:32,279
Hello?

319
00:34:32,862 --> 00:34:34,197
Sir, please!

320
00:34:47,460 --> 00:34:50,839
And I got my wife back as a lifeless body.

321
00:34:56,553 --> 00:34:57,762
So you're saying…

322
00:34:58,722 --> 00:34:59,973
Yeah, it's him.

323
00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:03,602
The same man you're hunting right now.

324
00:35:04,394 --> 00:35:07,147
Since that day,
he's all I've thought about.

325
00:35:07,897 --> 00:35:10,191
The only reason
I'm still breathing is to catch him.

326
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:16,114
And then, one day,
I heard his voice again.

327
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:39,012
Hello?

328
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:41,555
Where are you, Mr. Kang?

329
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:44,892
Oh, I'm at my in-laws' house right now.

330
00:35:44,893 --> 00:35:45,976
In-laws?

331
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:49,606
They managed to prepare the money.

332
00:35:51,024 --> 00:35:52,025
Listen to me.

333
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:55,737
You're going to pay
for disappointing me until the end.

334
00:35:56,279 --> 00:35:58,948
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal, boss.

335
00:35:59,491 --> 00:36:01,242
And now, your wife's going to die.

336
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:08,165
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal, boss.

337
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,792
And now, your wife's going to die.

338
00:36:09,793 --> 00:36:12,170
Hey, Kang Taeju.

339
00:36:13,546 --> 00:36:14,714
This is on you.

340
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:18,677
Detective.

341
00:36:20,136 --> 00:36:21,596
Just know this.

342
00:36:22,931 --> 00:36:24,766
What happened to your wife

343
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:27,811
is all on you.

344
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:34,984
It was the same voice…

345
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,618
The same cadence and tone…

346
00:36:45,829 --> 00:36:47,580
from six years ago.

347
00:37:01,845 --> 00:37:03,178
These are the internal files

348
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:05,932
on the two cases
that bastard pulled before.

349
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:14,190
One's the murder of my wife.

350
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:17,736
The other is a case
we suspect he's behind.

351
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:23,324
The Seokdong Lake kidnapping
and murder from five years ago.

352
00:37:35,378 --> 00:37:37,254
ESTIMATED TOD
37-38 HRS AFTER RANSOM CALL

353
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,631
Exact same MO.

354
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:48,725
His window for murder is
36 to 38 hours post-ransom call.

355
00:37:49,559 --> 00:37:53,937
It's already been 15 hours
since he took your wife.

356
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:57,817
Why do you think he kidnapped her?

357
00:37:59,152 --> 00:38:00,153
Beats me.

358
00:38:00,987 --> 00:38:02,781
Who knows what this guy is thinking?

359
00:38:04,574 --> 00:38:06,576
But one thing is for sure.

360
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,371
Your wife is still alive.

361
00:38:11,164 --> 00:38:12,874
Though she doesn't have much time left.

362
00:38:19,672 --> 00:38:21,758
So what do I have to do now

363
00:38:22,383 --> 00:38:24,135
to save my wife?

364
00:38:25,845 --> 00:38:27,263
First, you lure him out.

365
00:38:27,931 --> 00:38:29,933
But I don't even know where he is.

366
00:38:31,684 --> 00:38:33,520
You're going to cut him a deal.

367
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:37,564
At around 10:20 p.m.
at Ilseo Industrial Complex,

368
00:38:37,565 --> 00:38:38,649
a standoff erupted

369
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:40,734
between police and a neurosurgeon…

370
00:38:40,735 --> 00:38:44,738
…suspected of orchestrating
his wife's kidnapping and murder.

371
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:46,990
The suspect disarmed an officer…

372
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:47,992
Mr. Kang?

373
00:38:49,369 --> 00:38:50,452
He's good.

374
00:38:50,453 --> 00:38:53,705
He may have slipped into nearby
residential or busy commercial districts.

375
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:55,917
Citizens are urged
to exercise extreme caution.

376
00:39:57,729 --> 00:39:59,188
TUESDAY, FEBRUARY 10
ALARM

377
00:41:27,068 --> 00:41:29,736
Hey, are you ready?

378
00:41:29,737 --> 00:41:33,615
Punish me, O Great Spirit,
for I have sinned.

379
00:41:33,616 --> 00:41:36,451
I vowed to serve
and follow you and you only.

380
00:41:36,452 --> 00:41:39,788
Yet, I was foolish enough
to seek another deity.

381
00:41:39,789 --> 00:41:42,791
Please punish me,
for death is the only way--

382
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:48,839
No.

383
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:51,842
No.

384
00:41:51,843 --> 00:41:53,176
No!

385
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:54,261
Stop it!

386
00:41:54,262 --> 00:41:56,930
No! Don't do it!

387
00:41:56,931 --> 00:41:58,765
Please don't do this!

388
00:41:58,766 --> 00:42:03,938
Please don't do this, please!

389
00:42:08,317 --> 00:42:09,318
Ms. Lee Seonja?

390
00:42:10,653 --> 00:42:11,988
Please say something.

391
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:15,783
Please say something, Ms. Lee.

392
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:21,705
Ms. Lee…

393
00:42:24,125 --> 00:42:26,752
Screw you, you sick freak!

394
00:42:26,753 --> 00:42:28,003
Just kill me!

395
00:42:28,004 --> 00:42:29,588
Kill me too!

396
00:42:49,317 --> 00:42:51,943
Hey, Captain.
Looking at the surveillance footage,

397
00:42:51,944 --> 00:42:54,362
it looks like after Kang
fled the industrial complex,

398
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:58,241
he entered a nearby subway station,
got off at Shinyu Station,

399
00:42:58,242 --> 00:43:00,952
and then headed toward
the open lot right by the underpass.

400
00:43:00,953 --> 00:43:04,372
But there are no cameras
from the underpass to the lot,

401
00:43:04,373 --> 00:43:05,875
so we lost him here.

402
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:08,293
Yeah, we're sweeping the perimeter,

403
00:43:08,294 --> 00:43:11,463
but with all the blind spots
and the outdated cameras in this area,

404
00:43:11,464 --> 00:43:13,800
we still can't lock down his exact route.

405
00:43:14,717 --> 00:43:17,637
- Go back to the footage from the station.
- Yes, sir.

406
00:43:21,057 --> 00:43:23,016
He definitely went there to meet someone.

407
00:43:23,017 --> 00:43:25,853
When perps are on the run, they just run.

408
00:43:26,395 --> 00:43:28,397
They don't stop to look at maps.

409
00:43:29,899 --> 00:43:34,070
It's possible he's got another accomplice
who knows where the blind spots are.

410
00:43:34,737 --> 00:43:35,738
Another accomplice?

411
00:43:37,031 --> 00:43:39,991
Check if any
of the local residents are ex-convicts.

412
00:43:39,992 --> 00:43:41,702
They likely left together in a vehicle.

413
00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:45,330
Oh, and pull every plate captured
within a five-kilometer radius

414
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:47,582
at this hour and run background checks.

415
00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:49,167
-  Yes, sir.
- We're on it.

416
00:43:49,168 --> 00:43:51,461
Police have released
citizen footage showing

417
00:43:51,462 --> 00:43:54,172
Kang brandishing a weapon
and terrorizing bystanders.

418
00:43:54,173 --> 00:43:56,633
We got to run!

419
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:58,301
Dude, I think he's crazy.

420
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:01,138
Officials say Kang is armed
and extremely unstable…

421
00:44:01,139 --> 00:44:03,723
Geez, that damn psycho.

422
00:44:03,724 --> 00:44:06,309
He's going to burn in hell.

423
00:44:27,248 --> 00:44:30,877
Geez, give me a break already.

424
00:44:45,266 --> 00:44:49,437
What are you…

425
00:44:50,146 --> 00:44:51,814
Let's step inside, Father.

426
00:44:55,193 --> 00:44:56,611
Honey, what's going on?

427
00:44:57,195 --> 00:44:58,196
Everything okay?

428
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:04,618
Are you out of your mind?
How dare you point a gun at me!

429
00:45:04,619 --> 00:45:05,620
Step inside.

430
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:07,788
Taeju.

431
00:45:08,789 --> 00:45:09,790
What…

432
00:45:12,168 --> 00:45:13,169
Where's Seyun?

433
00:45:14,670 --> 00:45:16,505
Where is she right now?

434
00:45:17,506 --> 00:45:18,883
Don't move, Mother.

435
00:45:20,134 --> 00:45:21,761
I can't tell you anything right now.

436
00:45:22,929 --> 00:45:24,388
What do you want then?

437
00:45:25,097 --> 00:45:27,475
Why the hell are you here with a gun?

438
00:45:28,976 --> 00:45:29,977
To pick up the money.

439
00:45:30,645 --> 00:45:32,438
What? Money?

440
00:45:33,397 --> 00:45:35,066
The three billion you have here.

441
00:45:35,983 --> 00:45:37,943
I need you to hand it over to me.

442
00:45:37,944 --> 00:45:39,445
You're going to cut him a deal.

443
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:41,196
What?

444
00:45:41,197 --> 00:45:44,659
But before you do that, you have
to let him know you've got the money.

445
00:45:45,618 --> 00:45:50,080
"A famous doctor suspected
of kidnapping and murdering his wife

446
00:45:50,081 --> 00:45:53,417
flees questioning
and even steals from his in-laws…"

447
00:45:54,168 --> 00:45:56,253
That will definitely make the headline.

448
00:45:56,254 --> 00:45:57,754
And you have to really sell it.

449
00:45:57,755 --> 00:46:01,092
Make it look like you actually
kidnapped your own wife.

450
00:46:02,051 --> 00:46:05,471
You might have to do
more than just take the money.

451
00:46:06,973 --> 00:46:08,266
The three billion?

452
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:12,019
So it was about money.

453
00:46:12,687 --> 00:46:14,397
Now I'm getting it.

454
00:46:15,231 --> 00:46:18,442
You got close to Seyun
for money from the start, right?

455
00:46:19,735 --> 00:46:21,695
See, honey? What did I tell you?

456
00:46:21,696 --> 00:46:24,365
I kept telling you that he was bad news.

457
00:46:25,366 --> 00:46:27,617
You're finally showing your true colors.

458
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:30,287
You kept up the act pretty well, huh?

459
00:46:30,288 --> 00:46:31,789
What a performance!

460
00:46:32,707 --> 00:46:33,999
Taeju.

461
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:37,252
If you want the money, let Seyun go first.

462
00:46:37,253 --> 00:46:39,254
Then I'll give you the money. All of it!

463
00:46:39,255 --> 00:46:40,298
No, Mother.

464
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:43,508
Give me the money first.
That's the only way she'll live.

465
00:46:43,509 --> 00:46:44,677
What?

466
00:46:45,303 --> 00:46:49,180
You greedy bastard. Rot in hell!

467
00:46:49,181 --> 00:46:53,435
Taeju. How did you end up like this?

468
00:46:53,436 --> 00:46:55,228
Is this who you really are?

469
00:46:55,229 --> 00:47:00,108
I mean, this is just…
I can't believe this is happening.

470
00:47:00,109 --> 00:47:03,945
There's no point in talking
to this subhuman garbage.

471
00:47:03,946 --> 00:47:05,031
I'm calling the cops.

472
00:47:06,073 --> 00:47:07,283
I wouldn't do that, Father!

473
00:47:08,951 --> 00:47:10,160
"Father"?

474
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:13,121
Don't you dare call me that!

475
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:15,291
Have you no shame at all?

476
00:47:16,208 --> 00:47:17,626
I said don't do it!

477
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:20,546
What? You're going to shoot me?

478
00:47:21,088 --> 00:47:23,424
Go on then. Shoot me!

479
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:25,967
Shoot me, you bastard!

480
00:47:25,968 --> 00:47:28,470
Oh, honey, don't. Please, just…

481
00:47:28,471 --> 00:47:30,639
- You don't have the guts, do you?
-  Please.

482
00:47:42,026 --> 00:47:44,445
Stop! Taeju!

483
00:47:45,196 --> 00:47:47,281
Please stop.

484
00:47:48,991 --> 00:47:50,576
Stay exactly where you are.

485
00:47:51,077 --> 00:47:52,786
Just take it!

486
00:47:52,787 --> 00:47:54,622
Please, just take the money!

487
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:07,843
Go on, take it.

488
00:48:08,803 --> 00:48:09,887
Look at you.

489
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,556
What would your mother say if she saw you?

490
00:48:14,058 --> 00:48:15,392
Is this what she gets

491
00:48:15,393 --> 00:48:19,313
for breaking her back all by herself,
trying to raise you right?

492
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:23,651
Just answer me this.

493
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:27,655
Is Seyun still alive?

494
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:31,909
You could at least tell us that.

495
00:48:32,785 --> 00:48:34,286
Is she still alive?

496
00:48:37,540 --> 00:48:39,375
I believe so.

497
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:41,168
What?

498
00:48:41,794 --> 00:48:44,839
What do you mean?

499
00:48:46,841 --> 00:48:47,842
Huh?

500
00:49:33,262 --> 00:49:36,348
LAW ENFORCEMENT

501
00:49:58,871 --> 00:50:01,874
Did he tell you anything
when he took the money?

502
00:50:03,209 --> 00:50:05,043
He was just here for the money.

503
00:50:05,044 --> 00:50:06,962
He even opened fire inside this house.

504
00:50:07,463 --> 00:50:09,547
He was in no state
to say anything sensible.

505
00:50:09,548 --> 00:50:11,717
And where have you people been?

506
00:50:12,927 --> 00:50:15,637
Are you even trying to catch this bastard?

507
00:50:15,638 --> 00:50:17,305
Well, we're doing everything we can.

508
00:50:20,142 --> 00:50:21,976
What if she dies?

509
00:50:21,977 --> 00:50:24,313
What if my daughter dies?

510
00:50:25,648 --> 00:50:27,566
What will you do then?

511
00:50:29,735 --> 00:50:31,946
He said he "believed so."

512
00:50:33,697 --> 00:50:34,948
Pardon?

513
00:50:34,949 --> 00:50:37,785
My husband asked him if Seyun was alive,

514
00:50:38,619 --> 00:50:40,788
and he said, "I believe so."

515
00:50:41,664 --> 00:50:43,749
Those were his words.

516
00:50:45,376 --> 00:50:46,377
He

517
00:50:47,795 --> 00:50:49,046
"believes so"?

518
00:51:01,308 --> 00:51:02,726
How are you?

519
00:51:05,938 --> 00:51:09,274
Wanted fugitive Kang Taeju,
who fled while being questioned

520
00:51:09,275 --> 00:51:12,068
over allegations of plotting
his wife's kidnapping and murder,

521
00:51:12,069 --> 00:51:15,154
is confirmed to have broken into
his in-laws' home early this morning

522
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:17,824
and stolen billions of won in cash.

523
00:51:17,825 --> 00:51:19,993
Authorities say Kang fired
a stolen police weapon

524
00:51:19,994 --> 00:51:22,245
during the break-in
to threaten his parents-in-law,

525
00:51:22,246 --> 00:51:24,330
leaving the public in shock.

526
00:51:24,331 --> 00:51:26,457
Kang Taeju, a wanted fugitive

527
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:27,917
and a prominent local neurosurgeon…

528
00:51:27,918 --> 00:51:30,962
Dr. Ha, did you see that?

529
00:51:30,963 --> 00:51:33,590
I knew something like this would happen.

530
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:35,926
I told you he's crazy.
I knew he'd snap one day.

531
00:51:36,510 --> 00:51:37,928
That's not who he is.

532
00:51:39,013 --> 00:51:40,889
You're a terrible judge of character.

533
00:51:43,225 --> 00:51:44,560
Oh, look who it is.

534
00:51:45,185 --> 00:51:47,979
I heard they've been hitting it off
when he's on call.

535
00:51:47,980 --> 00:51:49,731
The rumors must be true.

536
00:51:50,858 --> 00:51:52,191
He's one of a kind.

537
00:51:52,192 --> 00:51:53,193
One of a kind indeed.

538
00:51:54,570 --> 00:51:55,571
Dr. Im.

539
00:51:56,822 --> 00:51:58,698
Things are already pretty tense right now.

540
00:51:58,699 --> 00:52:00,534
Don't go starting baseless rumors.

541
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:03,703
Right, okay.

542
00:52:03,704 --> 00:52:06,581
Not only did police
carelessly lose track of the suspect,

543
00:52:06,582 --> 00:52:09,125
but authorities were virtually helpless

544
00:52:09,126 --> 00:52:11,544
as he scored a firearm right
in the heart of the city

545
00:52:11,545 --> 00:52:13,797
and went on to commit
another major offense.

546
00:52:14,965 --> 00:52:17,342
I was woken up by the loud blasts.

547
00:52:17,343 --> 00:52:19,552
I thought it was fireworks.

548
00:52:19,553 --> 00:52:22,263
Citizens are expressing
absolute terror over the fact that

549
00:52:22,264 --> 00:52:26,393
a violent criminal is actively roaming
the streets while armed with a gun.

550
00:52:41,283 --> 00:52:43,077
You made it onto the news.

551
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:47,748
The culprit must've seen it too.

552
00:52:50,334 --> 00:52:52,251
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

553
00:53:01,387 --> 00:53:04,890
REVEALING THE TRUTH
WITH THE POWER OF SCIENCE

554
00:53:10,145 --> 00:53:11,146
The NFS?

555
00:53:11,605 --> 00:53:13,982
You want me to go there? Why?

556
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:16,694
To find the bait to lure him out.

557
00:53:25,869 --> 00:53:27,954
REQUEST FOR INVESTIGATION COOPERATION

558
00:53:27,955 --> 00:53:30,040
1. CASE NUMBER, 2026-9825
2. REQUESTED EVIDENCE

559
00:53:50,436 --> 00:53:54,439
Hi, I'm with Seongjin Police.
I'm here to urgently collect the evidence.

560
00:53:54,440 --> 00:53:56,442
Okay, give me a moment.

561
00:54:01,655 --> 00:54:02,865
Mmm. That's odd.

562
00:54:03,949 --> 00:54:06,034
I don't see anything in the system.

563
00:54:06,702 --> 00:54:07,785
Sorry?

564
00:54:07,786 --> 00:54:10,414
We should've received
an evidence release request first.

565
00:54:11,248 --> 00:54:12,249
Oh.

566
00:54:13,167 --> 00:54:16,295
No way, that's not possible.
We definitely sent in the form.

567
00:54:17,171 --> 00:54:18,839
Seongjin Police, right?

568
00:54:19,631 --> 00:54:22,508
Yeah, I'm with Seongjin Police.

569
00:54:22,509 --> 00:54:23,635
My name is Choi Hyeonsu.

570
00:54:39,818 --> 00:54:41,445
Hi, Chief. Are you busy?

571
00:54:42,362 --> 00:54:44,448
Yeah, I just want
to check something with you.

572
00:54:46,450 --> 00:54:49,328
Yeah, the case number is 2026-9825.

573
00:55:01,673 --> 00:55:04,133
Sir, where are you going?

574
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:06,386
Oh, they caught that punk.

575
00:55:08,764 --> 00:55:11,141
- You're all clear.
- What?

576
00:55:12,017 --> 00:55:13,101
Your request.

577
00:55:14,019 --> 00:55:15,145
Ah.

578
00:55:15,687 --> 00:55:18,565
Looks like there was a hiccup
on your side of the system.

579
00:55:19,650 --> 00:55:20,858
I see.

580
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:24,111
We still have to process it first,
but since you said it's urgent,

581
00:55:24,112 --> 00:55:25,739
I'll go grab the evidence for you.

582
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:29,158
- How can I help you?
-  Oh, hey.

583
00:55:29,159 --> 00:55:31,661
It's about case number 2026-5214.
A robbery case.

584
00:55:31,662 --> 00:55:33,579
SUHYEONG
IT'S DONE

585
00:55:33,580 --> 00:55:34,748
It's done.

586
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:17,707
Hungry, right?

587
00:56:22,838 --> 00:56:24,756
It's about time you got hungry.

588
00:56:27,217 --> 00:56:30,429
Well, I thought you would be,
so I grabbed some food.

589
00:56:38,645 --> 00:56:39,646
Take it.

590
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:42,941
Come on, take it.

591
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:47,696
Oh, right. I'm so stupid.
I forgot I tied your hands up.

592
00:56:48,697 --> 00:56:49,865
What do I do about that?

593
00:56:51,992 --> 00:56:55,787
So why did you do something so stupid?
Now I want to kill you.

594
00:57:03,795 --> 00:57:06,423
Ms. Ko. Listen.

595
00:57:07,257 --> 00:57:11,637
I know exactly what you're thinking
and doing, wherever you are.

596
00:57:32,366 --> 00:57:33,367
Right.

597
00:57:34,785 --> 00:57:36,453
Don't let the cream bun go to waste.

598
00:57:39,623 --> 00:57:40,832
Better eat it soon.

599
00:58:14,783 --> 00:58:15,784
Listen.

600
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:21,623
I know exactly what you're thinking
and doing, wherever you are.

601
00:58:36,012 --> 00:58:38,432
RENOWNED NEUROSURGEON
INFILTRATES THE NFS

602
00:58:39,015 --> 00:58:42,143
What on earth is this guy doing? Geez…

603
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:16,635
THE HUSBAND

604
00:59:56,676 --> 01:00:01,222
It's three billion won, just as promised.
You're saying you don't want it, right?

605
01:00:01,223 --> 01:00:04,600
Kang Taeju, you prick. I'm going
to make sure it's slow and painful.

606
01:00:04,601 --> 01:00:07,770
There's not much time.

607
01:00:07,771 --> 01:00:10,397
Don't react to him. Just wait.

608
01:00:10,398 --> 01:00:12,567
That's the only way
you can save your wife.

609
01:00:13,902 --> 01:00:15,486
No!

610
01:00:15,487 --> 01:00:16,571
Get out of here!

611
01:00:17,405 --> 01:00:18,865
This is the end of our deal.

612
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:21,493
Kang Taeju, stop!

613
01:00:24,037 --> 01:00:25,120
Don't come close!

614
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:27,540
Mr. Kang, it's already over.

615
01:00:27,541 --> 01:00:28,625
It's too late.

616
01:00:29,167 --> 01:00:31,169
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon
